Sierra Cybernetics is seeking a Senior Business Systems Analyst to work for us at our government client’s site in downtown San Francisco.  You will be responsible for maintenance and support, cloud migration activities, and new projects supporting our client’s specialized SAP SharePoint site.  

You should have experience creating business and technical requirements documents and project plans; reviewing and updating functional specifications and test scripts for new technology deployments; providing support for third-party vendors and business partners; and performing maintenance and operations support. 

You will also be responsible for the review and analysis of technology requests for new and existing interfaces for the SharePoint site and for identifying issues related to the development and maintenance of information technology systems that support our client’s business functions at our client’s site. You will ensure that the SharePoint Site has current content; users have appropriate access as needed and all users are proficient and effectively using the SharePoint site.

This assignment is expected to last 1 – 2 years or more.

Minimum Job-Specific Skills/Qualifications Required (in order of relative importance):
Candidates shall demonstrate a proven track-record in:
1.	5 - 7 years’ experience as a Senior Business Systems Analyst and/or Project Manager.
2.	Principles of business systems analysis, configuration, integration, reporting, and queries; 
3.	Principles and best business practices of group facilitation and building consensus;
4.	Principles and techniques for the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) and SAP’s Implementation Life Cycle; 
5.	Principles and techniques of analyzing and documenting all product life cycle artifacts such as: functional business requirements, business cases, project charters, communication plans, test plans, detailed functional specifications; 
6.	Project management methods, tools, and techniques; 
7.	Business systems with multiple modules and business functional areas; 
8.	Advanced business process modeling; 
9.	Integrated system quality assurance methodologies; 
10.	Principles and techniques of creating project resource estimates and budgets; 
11.	Basic procurement processes including the creation of RFP, SOW, evaluation methodologies, contracts, and procurement documentation; 
12.	Basic networking technologies and data structures; 
13.	Principles of Web design and best practices for Web content management, tools and technologies, connectivity issues, browser issues; 
14.	Basic principles of relational databases and database reporting tools; 
15.	Principles and techniques of preparing a variety of effective written materials and oral presentations; 
16.	Best practices and emerging technologies in assigned area;
17.	Customer Service principles;
18.	Experienced with MS Office applications including Word, Excel, Project, and Visio;
19.	Knowledge of digital government and digital government strategies;
20.	Ability to identify and evaluate alternative solutions, costs and benefits;
21.	Ability to communicate effectively in English, orally and in writing.

Additional Skills/Qualifications Desired:
•	Experience working as an SAP Business Systems Analyst.
•	Recent experience within government agencies or public bodies with projects of a similar type.
•	Practical experience as a Senior Business Systems Analyst and/or Project Manager.
•	Project Management Professional (PMP) Certification.
•	Contract management for information technology products and services.
